      label: 'IPMasquerade',
      description: "Configures IP masquerading for the network interface. If enabled, packets forwarded from the network interface will be appear as coming from the local host. Typically, this should be enabled on the downstream interface of routers. Takes one of \"ipv4\", \"ipv6\", \"both\", or \"no\". Defaults to \"no\". Note that any positive boolean values such as \"yes\" or \"true\" are now deprecated. Please use one of the values above. Specifying \"ipv4\" or \"both\" implies IPv4Forwarding= settings in both .network file for this interface and the global networkd.conf(5) unless they are explicitly specified. Similarly for IPv6Forwarding= when \"ipv6\" or \"both\" is specified. See IPv4Forwarding=/IPv6Forwarding= in the above for the per-link settings, and networkd.conf(5) for the global settings.Added in version 219.",
