      label: 'IPv6PrivacyExtensions',
      description: "Configures use of stateless temporary addresses that change over time (see RFC 4941, Privacy Extensions for Stateless Address Autoconfiguration in IPv6). Takes a boolean or the special values \"prefer-public\" and \"kernel\". When true, enables the privacy extensions and prefers temporary addresses over public addresses. When \"prefer-public\", enables the privacy extensions, but prefers public addresses over temporary addresses. When false, the privacy extensions remain disabled. When \"kernel\", the kernel's default setting will be left in place. When unspecified, the value specified in the same setting in networkd.conf(5), which defaults to \"no\", will be used.Added in version 222.",
