      key: 'MulticastIGMPVersion',
      name: 'MulticastIGMPVersion', 
      label: 'MulticastIGMPVersion',
      description: "Configures IPv4 Multicast IGMP Version to be used, and controls the value of /proc/sys/net/ipv4/conf/INTERFACE/force_igmp_version. Takes one of \"no\", \"v1\", \"v2\", or \"v3\". When \"no\", no enforcement of an IGMP version is applied. IGMPv1/v2 fallbacks are allowed, and systemd-networkd will return to IGMPv3 mode after all IGMPv1/v2 Querier Present timers have expired. When \"v1\", use of IGMP version 1 is enforced. An IGMPv1 report will be returned even if IGMPv2/v3 queries are received. When \"v2\", use of IGMP version 2 is enforced. An IGMPv2 report will be returned if an IGMPv2/v3 query is received. systemd-networkd will fall back to IGMPv1 if an IGMPv1 query is received. When \"v3\", use of IGMP version 3 is enforced, and the response is the same as with \"no\". Defaults to unset — the sysctl is not set. Added in version 257.",
